annotations: I pull up on your mama like Stacy’s

This is most likely a reference to the song “Stacy’s Mom” by Fountains of Wayne, released in 2003. Throughout the song, the narrator explains that he’s in love with his friend Stacy’s mom, “who’s got it goin' on”.
I’m tryna have my baby with Gravy
She to have sex with him and get pregnant
Why you so cold like the AC?
He is referring to himself being cold because of the jewelry and watches he owns, which are referred to as ice, this makes him in himself cold.

Could pull up to your crib with the Baileys
 We could watch some Martin Scorsese
Baileys is a type of alcohol that white women drink and he’s also stunting cause he paid an extra dollar for the hd which very few people do
And we bumping Al Green, now I’m Al Gravy

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al_Green

Al Green was a popular music artist in the 1970’s. Gravy’s music takes some inspiration from him and that is why he’s calling himself Al Gravy.
Gravy just met her at Macy’s
Macy’s is an American department store chain founded in 1858 by Rowland Hussey Macy. It’s popular with older moms, hence why it was used after mentioning ‘Stacys mama’. Godlike word play.

description.plain: This song was first previewed during tobi’s Billboard takeover, in which he posted to the @billboardhiphop Instagram account. The Instagram story featured him riding on a bike while playing unreleased music. He showed off a total of 4 songs. With Student Loans being the first. The third song previewed was this song, “NOTICE ME feat. MIA GLADSTONE”. At this time, the 2 others have not yet been released, but it can be assumed that these will appear on his upcoming album, the same project this song is on Parrish Blue. The music video was also teased several hours before its release on tobi’s Instagram story.

body.plain: This song was first previewed during tobi’s Billboard takeover, in which he posted to the @billboardhiphop Instagram account. The Instagram story featured him riding on a bike while playing unreleased music. He showed off a total of 4 songs. With Student Loans being the first. The third song previewed was this song, “NOTICE ME feat. MIA GLADSTONE”. At this time, the 2 others have not yet been released, but it can be assumed that these will appear on his upcoming album, the same project this song is on Parrish Blue. The music video was also teased several hours before its release on tobi’s Instagram story.

annotations:
I only fuck with the real ones (Sunshine hit my face)
 I do not fuck with no pilgrims (Put a nigga in his place)

Tobi is saying how he only likes to be around authentic people. He spins this into a critique of colonialism when he says “I do not fuck with no pilgrims.” While pilgrims is a very general term, in the USA it usually refers to the early English settlers at Plymouth Rock. The juxtaposition of pilgrims and “real ones” is pointing out that they and their cultural and genetic descendants are not the original  residents of the USA and effectively stole the land which they own through one-sided trades with ill informed natives and genocide.
My 808 bang on your ear drum (Wind blowin’ through my hair)

While simply just referring to how bassy an 808 is and how tobi uses 808s in the vast majority of his songs, this is likely also referencing a few lines from the first single on Parrish Blue, Uncle Iroh. Where tobi says something similar:

Who that bangin in the whip? (That’s me)
…
My shit different when it hit (Slide)
And I’m up like Tylenol PM (Do you remember how we would get up in the sunshine?)

A reference to the product, “TYLENOL PM Extra Strength”, a high strength nighttime pain reliever and sleep aid.



Mia’s ad-lib here serves as being reminiscent of better times, mentioning how her and another person used to get up at regular times in the morning. And tobi’s line references needing pills to aid sleep. This creates a nice bit of contrast.
The grass is greener with you by my side (I want you by my side)

A play on the classic phrase “the grass is always greener on the other side”. A saying that means that other things will always look more appealing than what one already has. Instead being said here as meaning that with whoever GLADSTONE’s significant other is, she has no desire for anybody else.
